        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28339",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dmuir",
                        "name": "dmuir",
                        "displayName": "David Muir",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I was able to get unions working by using this syntax:\n\n{noformat}\n$selectA = $db->select()\n    ->from(array('u' => 'user'), 'name')\n    ->where('u.id >= 5');\n\n$selectB = $db->select()\n    ->from(array('u' => 'user'), 'name')\n    ->where('u.id < 5');\n\n$select = $db->select()\n    ->union(array($selectA, $selectB));\n{noformat}\n\nor alternatively\n\n{noformat}\n$select = $db->select()\n    ->union(array(\n        $db->select()\n            ->from(array('u' => 'user'), 'name')\n            ->where('u.id >= 5'),\n        $db->select()\n            ->from(array('u' => 'user'), 'name')\n            ->where('u.id < 5')\n        ));\n\n{noformat}\n\nIt won't wrap each select clause in parenthesis though. See ZF-4338 for that issue.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dmuir",
                        "name": "dmuir",
                        "displayName": "David Muir",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-01-20T17:10:44.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-01-20T17:10:44.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34560",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=beberlei",
                        "name": "beberlei",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Eberlei",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This is mainly a documentation issue. The union() method doc comment described functionality it did not have.\n\nThe only working example for union is to pass an array of sql query strings or Zend_Db_Select instances into its first parameter and render that.\n\nI have added documentation on the issue into the Zend_Db_Select manual.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=beberlei",
                        "name": "beberlei",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Eberlei",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-09-17T14:04:58.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-09-17T14:04:58.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
